Package: picam-orchestrator
Version: 1.0.0+202606221547
Architecture: arm64
Maintainer: Jaco Hanekom <jhanekom@gmail.com>
Installed-Size: 161
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.34), libgcc-s1 (>= 3.0), libjpeg62-turbo (>= 1.3.1), libstdc++6 (>= 11), picam-raw, picam-hailo
Section: video
Priority: optional
Description: MJPEG stream + camera control backend for picam-raw + picam-hailo
 Headless backend exposing Main / Lores / Annotated MJPEG streams over
 plain HTTP (/stream?stream=main|lores|annotated), a JSON status
 endpoint (/status.json), an on-the-fly OSD toggle (/osd), and a
 camera-switch proxy to picam-raw (/camera?id=N). No web interface of
 its own. Each connected client selects its stream independently.
 Main and Lores are live feeds straight from picam-raw; Annotated
 buffers the main stream for ~1 second, matches detections from
 picam-hailo by timestamp, and draws bounding boxes onto the delayed
 frames.
 .
 Install picam-frontend on one machine to get a browser UI that can
 view, switch streams/cameras, and toggle the OSD across multiple
 picam-orchestrator backends (e.g. several Pis) from one page.
 .
 Config: /etc/picam-orchestrator/config.ini
